📦 SBOM Parser (Bash + jq):

A simple Bash script to parse a JSON SBOM (Software Bill of Materials) and extract key security-relevant information.

This script is useful in DevSecOps pipelines to quickly analyze components, licenses, and structure of a software build.

🚀 Features:

The script provides the following functionalities:

📦 List all components (name + version)
📊 Count total number of components
📂 Display component types (OS, library, application, etc.)
🏷️ Extract license information
🛠️ Requirements

Make sure the following tools are installed:

bash
jq (JSON parser)
Install jq (if not installed)
sudo apt install jq        # Ubuntu/Debian
sudo dnf install jq        # RHEL/Fedora
brew install jq            # macOS

📄 Usage
1. Make script executable
chmod +x parse-sbom.sh
2. Run the script
./parse-sbom.sh sbom.json

📂 Expected SBOM Format:
The script assumes a JSON structure similar to Syft SBOM output:

{
  "artifacts": [
    {
      "name": "openssl",
      "version": "1.1.1",
      "type": "deb",
      "licenses": [{"value": "OpenSSL"}]
    }
  ]
}

📊 Example Output:
=== Component List ===
openssl:1.1.1
log4j:2.14.1
bash:5.1
flask:2.0.1

=== Total Component Count ===
4

=== Component Types ===
openssl:deb
log4j:java-archive
bash:deb
flask:python

=== Licenses ===
openssl:OpenSSL
log4j:Apache-2.0
bash:GPL-3.0
flask:BSD-3-Clause


🧠 How It Works:

The script uses jq to parse JSON and extract:

.artifacts[].name
.artifacts[].version
.artifacts[].type
.artifacts[].licenses[].value

Each operation is implemented as a separate Bash function for modularity and clarity.

🔐 DevSecOps Use Case:

This script can be integrated into a CI/CD pipeline to:

Gain visibility into dependencies
Support vulnerability scanning workflows
Validate license compliance
Prepare data for policy enforcement

⚠️ Notes:
The script assumes .artifacts[] format (used by Syft)
If your SBOM uses .components[], update jq queries accordingly

📌 Future Improvements:
Add vulnerability scan integration (Grype / Trivy)
Add policy enforcement (fail build on risky packages)
Export results to CSV or JSON
Support multiple SBOM formats


